    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by the premium matchups of Christian Yelich (75.84) and Yordan Alvarez (75.09). Yelich benefits from a significant boost against Bello, while Alvarez is primed to exploit a favorable park factor and SP skill mismatch against Feltner. Trea Turner (68.62) and Kyle Schwarber (66.48) round out the high-efficiency core, both capitalizing on positive Order spots and Houser\u2019s vulnerable pitching profile to drive Roto category production.\n\nConversely, the bottom of the order presents some volatility that requires monitoring. Pete Crow-Armstrong\u2019s matchup against McClanahan is the most concerning play on the board, as a negative platoon split combined with a low batting order position creates a potential sink for daily OBP and run production. Furthermore, while Caleb Durbin\u2019s projected SB contribution against Woodruff is theoretically high, his suppressed Order #7 spot makes him a borderline candidate to keep in the lineup if we need to prioritize safer volume elsewhere. Ensure all starters are confirmed against these right-handed SPs before first pitch to maintain maximum 5x5 leverage.",
